{"id":1840,"date":"2012-02-16T06:25:28","date_gmt":"2012-02-16T12:25:28","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mens_journal_gets_manlier.php"},"modified":"2012-02-16T06:25:28","modified_gmt":"2012-02-16T12:25:28","slug":"mens_journal_gets_manlier","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mens_journal_gets_manlier.php","title":{"rendered":"<em>Men&#8217;s Journal<\/em> Gets Manlier"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mens_journal_logo.gif\" alt=\"Men's Journal Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>First published in 1992, <em><a href=\"http:\/\/www.mensjournal.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Men&#8217;s Journal<\/a><\/em>, as its name implies is a lifestyle magazine for men with a circulation of more than 700,000 copies to an 84% male audience. Owned by Wenner Media, <em>Men&#8217;s Journal<\/em> is a sister publication to <em>Rolling Stone<\/em> and <em>Us Weekly<\/em>. Last week the magazine introduced a new logo designed by renown letterer Jim Parkinson &mdash; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.typedesign.com\/logos\/mensjournal.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">who previously drew one of the past versions of the logo<\/a> &mdash; in collaboration with <em>Men&#8217;s Journal<\/em> art director <a href=\"http:\/\/benjamen.net\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Benjamen Purvis<\/a>.<\/p><!--more--><blockquote>[They] took their inspiration from 1930s European auto-racing posters &mdash; rugged, elegant, unadorned. &#8220;It&#8217;s handcrafted, masculine, and authoritative,&#8221; Purvis says. &#8220;I think it perfectly expresses the spirit of our magazine.&#8221;<br \/>&mdash; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mensjournal.com\/introducing-our-new-look\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">&#8220;New Look&#8221; mention<\/a><\/blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mens_journal_cover.jpg\" alt=\"Men's Journal\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/mens_journal_cover_lg.jpg\" alt=\"Men's Journal\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The previous logo was good, falling in that red, graphically beveled look that Jim Parkinson has mastered over the years, most famously in his logo for sister publication <em>Rolling Stone<\/em> &mdash; although I don&#8217;t think Parkinson did the previous version, just the one before that. The new logo abandons the outlines, shadows, and dimensionality in favor of a bad-ass, bold, and condensed treatment. The combination of hard angles in the &#8220;S&#8221; and &#8220;R&#8221; coupled with the barely round corners gives the logo an extra masculine whiff that the previous logos lacked. The tracking and kerning is quite impeccable too and it looks great emblazoned across the width of the magazine&#8217;s cover.<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.hodgespart.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Tony Scida<\/a> for the tip.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_120216_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_120216_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_120216_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_120216_votes_02.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv2\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TABLE-->\n<img src=\"https: